1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:14,000
DeepBook Risk Console turns a risky trading workflow into a Sui-owned workflow.

2
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:30,000
The old workflow is broken: Sui has a powerful native order book, but builders need safer tools to translate strategies into auditable execution plans.

3
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:48,000
The wedge is small on purpose: DeepBook Risk Console packages that into a focused MVP: pool risk console and predict scenario scorer.

4
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:58,000
Now the actual local app opens to a dashboard, not a static background loop.

5
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:10,000
The walkthrough saves a policy, checks an agent request, and only then unlocks wallet approval.

6
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:24,000
The embedded wallet creates a key, requests local SUI, and signs the guarded transaction.

7
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:38,000
One object, one Move call, one digest per run. This is the Sui proof path, not just UI animation.

8
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:54,000
The submission ships as a standalone repo with app, contracts, scripts, subtitles, and video.

9
00:01:54,000 --> 00:02:06,000
Judge it as a shippable DeepBook wedge, not a slide deck.
